Test 1 - No Crypto Name Selection
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Skip Crypto Name spinner, enter correct data for other two text boxes
    7. Press submit button
    8. Error raised, "Invalid cryptocurrency selected"

Test 2 - No Quantity Purchased
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Skip Quantity Purchased text box, enter correct data for other two inputs
    7. Press submit button
    8. Error raised, "Quantity field requires a numerical value"

Test 3 - Non-numerical Value for Quantity Purchased
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Enter correct data into Crypto Name spinner and Date Purchased text box
    7. Enter string into Quantity Purchased text box
    8. Press submit button
    9. Error raised, "Quantity field requires a numerical value"

Test 4 - No Date Purchased
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Skip Date Purchased text box, enter correct data for other two inputs
    7. Press submit button
    8. Error raised, "Invalid date format. Use YYYY-MM-DD"

Test 5 - Wrong Date Format
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Enter correct data into Crypto Name spinner and Quantity Purchased text box
    7. Enter an invalid date format into Date Purchased text box (i.e. 05/07/2025)
    8. Press submit button
    9. Error raised, "Invalid date format. Use YYYY-MM-DD"

Test 6 - Successful Portfolio Entry
    1. Run database_installer
    2. Run the main app
    3. Either create new profile or select existing user
    4. Press login button
    5. Click on New Portfolio Entry Button
    6. Enter correct data into Crypto Name spinner, Quantity Purchased text box, and Date Purchased text box
    7. Press submit button
    8. Message displayed, "Submitted"